g.text: {{Natural language} A StateMachine may not be
a method and, if it has a context, it must be a
{{Natural language} The triggers of a Transition must
all be for CallEvents or SignalEvents.}
CallEvents on the triggers of a Transition must be
owned or inherited by the context of the containing
{{Natural language} If all triggers of a Transition are for SignalEvents, then
an effect Behavior of the Transition may have exactly one Parameter of
mode “in”, multiplicity upper bound of 1 and a type that is a Signal that
conforms to all the Signals of the Transition triggers. If all the triggers are
for CallEvents, such that the signatures of the Operations of the CallEvents
are consistent, then an effect Behavior may have a signature that conforms
to or input-conforms to all the signatures of the Operations of the
CallEvents. Otherwise, an effect Behavior must have no Parameters.}
{{Natural language} If all the relevant Triggers of an entry,
doActivity or effect Behavior are for SignalEvents, then the
Behavior may have exactly one Parameter of mode “in”, multiplicity
upper bound of 1 and a type that is a Signal that conforms to all
the Signals of the relevant Triggers. If all the relevant Triggers are
for CallEvents, such that the signatures of the Operations of the
CallEvents are consistent, then an entry or exit behavior Behavior
may have a signature that conforms to or input-conforms to all the
signatures of the Operations of the CallEvents and a doActivity
Behavior may have a signature that input-conforms to all the
signatures of the Operations of the CallEvents. Otherwise, an
entry, doActivity or exit Behavior must have no Parameters.}
{{Natural language} The Signals of any SignalEvents on the triggers of a
Transition must have matching Receptions that are owned or inherited by
the context of the containing StateMachine of the Transition.}
